ZH: 1. 他们的计划出了问题，只能倒退重新开始。
EN: Their plan went awry and they had to step back and start over.
ZH: 2. 这次考试结果让他感到很失望，让他觉得自己在倒退。
EN: The result of this exam disappointed him, making him feel like he was regressing.
ZH: 3. 在技术上倒退一步，反而有助于更好地理解问题。
EN: Taking a step back technically can actually help understand the issue better.
ZH: 4. 现在不是倒退的时候，我们必须继续前进。
EN: Now is not the time to step back; we must continue moving forward.
ZH: 5. 在生活中遇到挫折并不可怕，只要不倒退就好。
EN: It's okay to face setbacks in life, as long as you don't regress.
ZH: 6. 每一次失败都是一个机会，要学会从中领悟而不是倒退。
EN: Every failure is an opportunity to learn, not a reason to back down.
ZH: 7. 只有在倒退的时候，我们才会反思自己的行为。
EN: It's only when we step back that we reflect on our actions.
ZH: 8. 面对挑战时，不要倒退，要敢于迈出第一步。
EN: When facing challenges, don't regress; dare to take the first step.
ZH: 9. 一旦倒退，就要付出更大的努力才能重新走回去。
EN: Once you step back, it takes more effort to move forward again.
ZH: 10. 在追求梦想的路上，永远不要向倒退妥协。
EN: On the journey to pursue your dreams, never compromise by regressing.
ZH: 11. 逆境是人生的一部分，但不是倒退的理由。
EN: Adversity is a part of life but not a reason to step back.
ZH: 12. 没有人可以避免失败，但是可以选择不倒退。
EN: No one can avoid failure, but you can choose not to regress.
ZH: 13. 成功的路上充满了挑战，决不能被击倒而倒退。
EN: The road to success is full of challenges; never be knocked down and regress.
ZH: 14. 生活的种种困难只是一种暂时的倒退，我们最终会走向成功。
EN: All the difficulties in life are just temporary setbacks; we will eventually move towards success.
ZH: 15. 他的失败并没有让他倒退，而是让他更加坚定了前进的步伐。
EN: His failure didn't cause him to regress; instead, it made him more determined to move forward.
ZH: 16. 面对失败时，坚强的人会选择向前看，而不是倒退。
EN: In the face of failure, strong individuals choose to look forward instead of stepping back.
ZH: 17. 即使遇到困难，我们也不能倒退，要坚持向前。
EN: Even when faced with difficulties, we should not regress but persevere and move forward.
ZH: 18. 没有人可以一路顺风，会有风雨，只是不能倒退。
EN: No one can have smooth sailing all the way; there will be storms, but we should not regress.
ZH: 19. 有时候倒退一步其实是为了更好地向前迈进。
EN: Sometimes taking a step back is actually to move forward better.
ZH: 20. 生活中的挫折教会我们不要倒退，而是更加努力地向前走。
EN: Setbacks in life teach us not to regress but to move forward with more effort.
